  <h3>1. Rent Smart Wales Registration (Mandatory)</h3>
  <table class="checklist-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Landlord registered with Rent Smart Wales</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">All landlords letting property in Wales must be registered with Rent Smart Wales. Registration lasts 5 years and requires identity verification.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Landlord/Agent licensed (if self-managing)</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">If you manage the property yourself, you must also hold a valid licence. If you use a licensed agent, they can manage on your behalf.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="legal-ref">Housing (Wales) Act 2014 | Rent Smart Wales</p>

  <h3>2. Written Statement (Mandatory)</h3>
  <table class="checklist-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Written statement provided within 14 days</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">Under the Renting Homes (Wales) Act 2016, you must provide a written statement setting out the terms of the occupation contract within 14 days of the occupation date. Failure to do so is a criminal offence.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>All fundamental and supplementary terms included</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">The written statement must include all statutory fundamental terms (which cannot be changed) and supplementary terms (which can be modified by agreement).</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="legal-ref">Renting Homes (Wales) Act 2016, ss.31-35</p>

  <h3>3. Deposit Protection (Mandatory)</h3>
  <table class="checklist-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Security deposit protected within 30 days</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">If you take a security deposit, you must protect it in an authorised tenancy deposit scheme within 30 days of receiving it.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Prescribed Information provided within 30 days</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">You must provide the contract-holder with the scheme's Prescribed Information within 30 days. Non-compliance prevents Section 173 possession notices.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="legal-ref">Renting Homes (Wales) Act 2016, ss.45-48</p>

  <h3>4. Gas Safety (Mandatory if gas supplied)</h3>
  <table class="checklist-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Valid Gas Safety Certificate (CP12)</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">A Gas Safe registered engineer must inspect all gas appliances annually. The certificate must be provided before the contract-holder moves in.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Copy provided before occupation</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">Contract-holders must receive a copy before moving in. Keep proof of provision.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="legal-ref">Gas Safety (Installation and Use) Regulations 1998</p>

  <h3>5. Energy Performance Certificate (EPC)</h3>
  <table class="checklist-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Valid EPC with minimum E rating</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">The dwelling must have an EPC rating of E or above. Properties rated F or G cannot be let unless a valid exemption is registered.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>EPC provided to contract-holder</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">Contract-holders must receive a copy of the EPC free of charge at the earliest opportunity.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="legal-ref">Energy Performance of Buildings (England and Wales) Regulations 2012 | MEES Regulations 2015</p>

  <h3>6. Electrical Safety (EICR)</h3>
  <table class="checklist-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Electrical Installation Condition Report (EICR)</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">From 1 December 2022, Wales requires private landlords to ensure electrical installations are inspected every 5 years and are in a satisfactory condition.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Copy provided within 28 days</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">New contract-holders must receive a copy before moving in. Existing contract-holders within 28 days of inspection.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="legal-ref">Renting Homes (Wales) Act 2016 (Fitness for Human Habitation) Regulations 2022</p>

  <h3>7. Fitness for Human Habitation</h3>
  <table class="checklist-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Dwelling fit for human habitation</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">Under the Renting Homes (Wales) Act, there is an implied term that the dwelling is fit for human habitation at the start of the occupation and will be kept fit throughout. This is a fundamental term.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Working smoke alarms on each storey</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">Smoke alarms must be installed on every storey used as living accommodation and must be in working order at the start of the contract.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Carbon monoxide alarms where required</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">CO alarms are required in rooms with fixed combustion appliances (excluding gas cookers).</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="legal-ref">Renting Homes (Wales) Act 2016, s.91</p>

  <h3>8. HMO Requirements (If applicable)</h3>
  <table class="checklist-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>HMO licence obtained (if required)</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">Properties housing 5+ people from 2+ households require a mandatory HMO licence. Some Welsh local authorities operate additional licensing schemes - check with your council.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Fire safety measures in place</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">HMOs require enhanced fire safety: fire doors, emergency lighting, fire alarms, and clear escape routes as specified in the licence conditions.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="legal-ref">Housing Act 2004 Part 2</p>

  <h3>9. Landlord Contact Details</h3>
  <table class="checklist-table">
    <tr>
      <td class="checkbox-cell">☐</td>
      <td>
        <strong>Landlord's name and address included in written statement</strong><br>
        <span class="guidance-text">The written statement must include the landlord's name and a correspondence address. If using an agent, the landlord's details must still be provided.</span>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <p class="legal-ref">Renting Homes (Wales) Act 2016, s.31(3)</p>

